-- AutoZone quarterly earnings rise
-- 
-- Tue Dec 5, 2006 8:34am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/12/05/businesspro-autozone-results-dc-idUSWEN071220061205

 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - AutoZone Inc. ( AZO.N ), the largest U.S. 
auto parts retail chain, said on Tuesday that quarterly 
earnings rose 8 percent as it focused on improving its parts 
inventory and pricing. 

  Net income rose to $123.9 million, or $1.73 per share, in 
its fiscal first quarter, ended November 18, from $114.4 
million, or $1.48 per share, a year earlier. Revenue rose 4.1 
percent to $1.39 billion.  Analysts, on average, expected AutoZone to report earnings 
of $1.68 per share on revenue of $1.39 billion, according to 
Reuters Estimates.  Sales at U.S. stores open at least one year, a key retail 
gauge known as same-store sales, rose 0.3 percent percent, the 
Memphis, Tennessee-based company said.  AutoZone, which had 3,912 stores at the end of the quarter, 
said that adjusted inventory per store increased to $503,000 
from $495,000 a year earlier.  Retail sales rose 3.9 percent to $1.17 billion, while sales 
to repair shops rose less than 1 percent to $160.7 million.  Shares of AutoZone closed at $114.47 on Monday on the New 
York Stock Exchange.